CleanShot Z has no external Swift dependencies. All application code is original
or uses Apple system frameworks (AppKit, SwiftUI, ScreenCaptureKit, Vision,
VisionKit, Core Graphics, Core Image, ImageIO, Carbon, ServiceManagement).

CleanShot Z runs entirely on-device: it makes no network calls, includes no
analytics or telemetry, and requires no account. Screenshots, recordings,
recognized text, and project files never leave the user's Mac.

CleanShot Z is an independent project. It is not affiliated with, endorsed by,
or connected to MTW (makers of CleanShot X); the name references the product
only to describe the category of tool CleanShot Z belongs to.
